This paper discusses the principle component analysis (PCA) as a deterministic input-output system, which is a common topic in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the information loss induced by PCA, which is related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of PCA in computer vision (cs.CV), statistics (cs.ST), and numerical analysis (cs.NA), which are all relevant sub-categories.
